            <article data-uuid="59fe9a1960df4f799f2b6a477579445e">
                <h3 data-uuid="c01d1cf71f75438a9736a1e434cf055e" class="eq">Essential Question</h3>
                <h3 data-uuid="734aef2c727942818c85da67e280b6b6" class="eqt">How did the Industrial Revolution help shape life
                    in the North?</h3>
                <p data-uuid="808cf6c6351643beaa93d18ee1fff268">In
                    the early 1800s the Industrial Revolution changed the way goods
                    were produced in the United States. Manufacturing grew
                    more quickly. New factories were built that changed how many Americans lived
                    and worked. Workers organized to ensure fair pay and working conditions. New
                    technology and inventions changed the way people traveled, communicated, and
                    did house work.&#160;</p>
                <p data-uuid="c53164abbecc4f05986ee721724afb8b">As you read this module, look for evidence of the changes brought by new technologies and inventions. Note the
                    key people, events, and circumstances of the Industrial Revolution that helped
                    shape life in the North. When you are done, you will write a short essay
                    answering the Essential Question for this module.</p>
            </article>
            <section data-uuid="74647a51fafa4c1991ecb508a605409c" class="video-container ">
                <article data-uuid="007c8f27ba4046dfae59cede552d5cfe">
                    <h3 data-uuid="95a462470eef4d64a230d69a83825d7d" class="vid">Industrial
                        Revolution</h3>
                    <p data-uuid="dd8f63d187394517a6a5428bc5285021">Prior to industrialization, all goods were
                        produced by hand. This changed in the late 18th and early 19th centuries when mechanization
                        transformed the textile industry. Later in the 1800s, mills and factories mass-produced a wide array of everyday items. Much of the nation, especially the North,
                        became an urban industrial society. Watch the video to learn about how the Industrial
                        Revolution reshaped American life.</p>
